config.content:
## Explore DCIM

1. Get to know the Amsterdam Site, Rack, Devices, Cables, Circuits, and more! Follow this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/DCIM/explore-amsterdam-site.md).
2. Follow this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/DCIM/explore-device-nlams-1-sw-1.md) to discover how NetBox models Devices.
3. Get hands on! Add a new Switch to the Rack in Amsterdam by following this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/DCIM/add-new-device.md).

**note** - for the best experience *right-click* the above links and open them in a new browser window

NetBox Cloud [settings](https://console.netboxlabs.com/)

NetBox Cloud [documentation](https://docs.netboxlabs.com/)

NetBox Cloud [support](support@netboxlabs.com)

## Explore IPAM

1. Follow this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/IPAM/explore-ipam-data.md) to learn how NetBox models IPAM Data like - RIRs, Prefixes, IP Addresses and VLANs
2. Get hands on! Assign an IP address to the Amsterdam router by following this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/IPAM/assign-ip-address.md)
3. Get hands on! Follow this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/IPAM/import-ipam-data.md) to create a VLAN Group and then bulk import VLANs and Prefixes from a spreadsheet 

**note** - for the best experience *right-click* the above links and open them in a new browser window

# Getting started with NetBox Cloud

Welcome to NetBox Cloud! If you're just starting your journey with NetBox, we have a number of tutorials designed to guide you step-by-step through its capabilities and show you how it can revolutionize your network documentation process. You'll find tutorials aligned to the three primary use cases for NetBox: DCIM, IPAM and Network Automation. We suggest jumping directly to the tutorial that most closely aligns with your current challenges. If you have any questions or just need help, please [reach out](mailto:support@netboxlabs.com)!

## Explore Network Automation

1. Follow this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/Network-Automation/explore-netbox-apis.md) to get familiar with the NetBox REST and GraphQL APIs
2. Learn how to use Config Contexts and Templates to render device configurations. See this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/Network-Automation/explore-provisioning.md)
3. Get hands on! Follow this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/Network-Automation/render-config-api.md) to render the configuration of a device using the REST API. 
4. Get hands on! Follow this [guide](https://github.com/netboxlabs/guided-trial/blob/develop/Network-Automation/add-webhook.md) to create and test a Webhook to an external system. 

**note** - for the best experience *right-click* the above links and open them in a new browser window
